# Tell GitHub Linguist how to classify project files.

# DAML source files — classify as DAML (requires Linguist >= 7.x).
# If GitHub doesn't recognise DAML yet, change to linguist-language=Haskell
# (DAML is syntactically Haskell-based) so the files appear in the language bar.
# *.daml linguist-language=DAML

# This tells GitHub to highlight Daml files as if they were Haskell. It's not
# perfect, but it's better than no syntax highlighting at all.
*.daml linguist-language=Haskell

# Cargo.lock is generated — exclude it from language stats so it doesn't
# artificially inflate the Rust percentage.
Cargo.lock linguist-generated=true
